com.vector.cfg.util.servicecontext

Interface IServiceContext

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.AutoCloseable, IDisposable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IApplicationContext, IProjectContext

    @ThreadSafe
 @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
public interface IServiceContext
extends IDisposable, java.lang.AutoCloseable
    Implementations of this interface allow retrieving system-wide services related to a specific context.

    Service registration is being handled via an extension point.

    (c) Copyright Vctr Informatik GmbH. All Rights Reserved.

    • Method Detail

      • addDisposeListener

        @KeepSecretFromPublishedApi
<T extends IServiceContext> void addDisposeListener(<any> listener)
        Adds a new dispose listener.

        The listener will be called, when this IServiceContext is disposed!

        Note: The Listeners are added via a WeakReference, so the listener is unregistered, if there is no other string reference to the IServiceContextDisposeListener.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the generic type
        Parameters:
        listener - the listener
        See Also:
        EVAL00100210

      • getAt

        @PublishedMethod
default <T> T getAt(java.lang.Class<T> service)
        Returns the requested service instance by the passed Class.

        This request is thread-safe and all threads share the requested service instances.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the instance to retrieve
        Parameters:
        service - the class of the requested service.
        Returns:
        service instance
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - - if the argument is null
        com.google.inject.ConfigurationException - if this IServiceContext cannot find or create the provider.
        com.google.inject.ProvisionException - if there was a runtime failure while providing an instance.
        See Also:
        getService(Class), getInstance(Class)
